            <h2 class="text-3xl mb-4">World War II and The Enigma Code</h2>
            <p class="text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                During World War II, Turing was a key figure at Bletchley Park, Britain's codebreaking center. He played a pivotal role in creating the "Bombe," an electro-mechanical device that helped decipher encrypted messages from the German Enigma machine. This work is credited with significantly shortening the war and saving countless lives.
            </p>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="https://placehold.co/400x250/d1d5db/374151?text=Bombe+Machine" alt="Image of the Bombe machine">
